    "To reduce the high computational demands and latency inherent in GNNs, MCond [27] adopts GC and proposes to learn a mapping from original nodes to condensed nodes.",
    "This approach allows direct information propagation on the small condensed graph, resulting in a significant acceleration of the inference process.5) Recommender Systems: Recommender systems are widely used in various industries such as e-commerce and social media, aiming to suggest relevant items or content to users.",
    "In a typical recommender system, the user-item interactions can be represented as a bipartite graph.",
    "As the number of users and items grows, this graph becomes increasingly large and complex, posing significant computational challenges.",
    "To handle this issue, Distill-CF [106] applies GC to recommender systems."
